Deputy head of the information security department of the Central Bank Artem Sychev said that the number was replaced by a wide range of Russian banks.
He explained that operators do not always respond to Central Bank warnings about fraudulent calls, citing the absence of such an obligation in the “On Communications” law.
In the bank "Open", Rosbank and Alpha-bank confirmed information about the increase in the number of fraudulent calls with the replacement of the number.
As reported in the press service "Bilan", part of the information on fraudulent calls that the Central Bank transmitted was incorrect: the lists included numbers that are actually used by banks to communicate with customers.
Blocking them would lead to disruptions in the organization.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of fraudulent numbers, to which the telecom operator will contact each call to verify the number.
He explained that the creation of such a base would require amendments to the legislation.
