Pavel Ustinov joined the pickets in support of the figures of the "Moscow case"
Actor Pavel Ustinov joined the series of single pickets "Freedom to All", which take place on Friday at the building of the administration of the President of the Russian Federation in the Old Square in Moscow, reports the correspondent of "Interfax".
The series of pickets began on September 18 in support of Ustinov himself and has since continued every day.
At present, the participants of the action, replacing each other, stand, holding in their hands a poster with the inscription "Freedom to all" and the names of the convicted and arrested after the uncoordinated protests in Moscow in the summer of 2019.
In addition to Ustinov, on the poster the names of Egor Zhukov, Kirilla Zhukov, Danil Begletsa, Evgeny Kovalenko, Konstantin Kotova, Ivan Podkopaev, Idar Gubaidulina, Aleksey Minyaylo, Sergei Fomina, Samariddin Rajabova.
The Tver court of Moscow on September 16 sentenced the 24-year-old Ustinov to 3.5 years of colony of the general regime on charges of using violence against the fighter OMON Rosgwardia in an uncoordinated action on August 3 in the center of Moscow (No. 2, article 318 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation).
Subsequently, on 20 September, at the request of the Prosecutor General ' s Office, the court changed Ustinov ' s restraint from being held in custody on a no-departure subscription.
So, the petition for the release of Ustinov received more than 112 thousand signatures per day.
The theater and cinema artists started a flashmob in support of colleagues.
To participate in a single picket in the sign of solidarity with the actor on September 18 in the Old Square was built the turn.
Human rights defenders, journalists, scientists, teachers, doctors, Orthodox priests demanded a review of the case.
As told Interfax sister Ustinov Yulia, at a rally on September 29 in the capital in support of the figures of the “Moscow case” her brother does not plan to speak.
“Sanctions” Deliveries to Russia fell 100 times
The Russian government estimated that supplies of agricultural products and food to Russia from countries that have fallen under the Russian food embargo have decreased more than 100 times since 2013.
According to a report sent to Russian President Vladimir Putin, in the first half of 2019, 31,000 tons of products were imported from sanctions countries against 3 million 442.2 thousand tons for the same period of 2013, reports Interfax.
At the same time, the value of imported products decreased to $226.5 million from $4.975.5 million, respectively.
We are talking about deliveries of goods that have not fallen under the embargo.
As indicated in the report, the volumes of the prohibited imports were compensated by the increase in imports from CIS countries, Africa, South-East Asia, and Serbia.
At the end of August, the government extended until December 31, 2020 the validity of the rules on the destruction of agricultural products, raw materials and food, which are prohibited from importing into Russia under counter-sanctions.
The document, posted on the official legal information portal, noted that the validity of the rules was extended by one more year - from December 31, 2019 to December 31, 2020.
Initially, the decision to destroy the sanction applied to products from the United States, the EU, Australia, Norway and Canada.
Later, since August 13, 2015, Albania, Montenegro, Iceland, Liechtenstein have "joined" this list, since January 1, 2016 - Ukraine.
Putin’s decree on the destruction of illegally imported “sanctions” (products that came under the food embargo that Moscow imposed in response to the anti-Russian sanctions of the West) came into force in 2015.
In turn, the government has allowed the destruction of “sanctioned” food in any legitimate way.
As the West maintains its sanctions, Russia has also extended its retaliatory measures.
At the same time, to products that citizens import for personal use, this measure does not apply.
The ban does not apply to the import of goods for personal consumption weighing up to 5 kilograms.
However, the head of the Council under the President of the Russian Federation on the development of civil society and human rights Mikhail Fedotov previously called "just immoral" destruction of food, and this, according to him, negatively affects the education of people.
Moreover, with the initiative to ban the destruction of food that is suitable for consumption, in early June, Rospotrebnadzor spoke.
A similar recommendation was then made to the Government by the Human Rights Council under the President of the Russian Federation.
And Deputy Prime Minister of Russia Alexey Gordeev said that destroying food is wrong, and it is necessary to think about how to use them on purpose, assessing the quality.
The head of the company is found guilty of tax evasion
According to the judgment of the Leninsky District Court of the city of Cheboksary, the director of the company "Land and law" 2 Vyacheslav Morozov is found guilty of committing the crimes provided for in paragraph "b" of Article 2 of the Constitution of the Russian Federation.
This is reported by the press service of the investigative department of the SCR in Chuvash.
From January 2008 to December 2009, Vyacheslav Morozov introduced information on unfinished transactions into the tax accounting documents of the LLC.
According to the fictitious documents, the company carried additional costs, and therefore, the amount of value added tax and profit of the organization was reduced 11.2 million rubles.
Vyacheslav Morozov was sentenced to 3.5 years in prison.
By 2023, the first school of a new format will be opened in the center of the capital
A new school will be opened in Khamovnik.
According to the head of Moscow investment Anastasia Pyatova, there will create all the conditions for self-realization and development of children’s talents.
The educational institution has decided to call it the “New View”.
This project will be curated by the Moscow State Institute of International Relations of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia and the Fund "Economic Development of the Higher School".
The design of the building with an area of about 10,000 "squares" is planned to begin next year.
Construction will be completed at the end of 2022, and the first students will begin to be recruited in the next year.
"The project provides for the creation of a public, non-profit educational space, which will be based on the traditions of the classical Moscow school and experimental methods," - noted in the press service of Moskostroyinvest.
In Chile, they began to build a telescope worth 1 billion euros.
This is reported by TASS with reference to the press service of the European Southern Observatory (ESO).
The European Extremely Large Telescope (EELT) is the most expensive and ambitious ground-based astronomical project, the European Extremely Large Telescope (EELT) said.
Its total cost, according to ESO, will exceed one billion euros.
Much of this money will be spent on the construction of the observatory’s building and equipment.
The most expensive and complex component of the telescope is its record-breaking mirror, whose diameter will be about 39 meters.
It will be assembled from 798 hexagonal segments measuring 1.4 meters.
This huge mirror, as well as two auxiliary reflective surfaces with a diameter of 4.2 and 3.75 meters, will help E-ELT get the first detailed photographs of planets outside the solar system, stars in other galaxies, as well as looking for Earth's twins.
In addition, scientists will try to use this observatory to observe the surroundings of Sgr A*, a supermassive black hole in the center of the Milky Way.
Despite the fact that the construction of the dome has only just begun, the mirrors, scientific tools and other components of the observatory have been developing for three years – since the announcement of the first plans for the construction of the E-ELT.
The contract for the production of the main mirror, which totalled about 400 million euros, was awarded to the German company SCHOTT and the French company Safran Reosc.
